The paper focuses on the BatchNorm component in training deep neural networks, which is a common technique used in machine learning and falls under the category of "Large Scale Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The experiments are conducted on image classification tasks, which fall under the category of "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV). The paper also explores the expressive power of neural networks, which falls under the categories of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing tasks, such as text classification, which falls under the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL).
